  "texts": [
    "The node types listed above do not include all of the classes that exist in each Open Biological and Biomedical Ontology (OBO) Foundry ontology.",
    "The Cell Ontology is included with the extended version of Uberon.",
    "a Two URIs are shown for pathways as the OBO Found ontology is the core ontology used to connect Reactome entities to the core set of OBO Foundry ontologies. b OBO node type.",
    "Includes all of the classes that are contained in the ontology even though they are not all explicitly listed here.",
    "Acronyms: CL (Cell ontology); CLO (Cell Line Ontology); CHEBI (Chemical Entities of Biological Interest); GO (Gene Ontology); HPO (Human Phenotype Ontology); MONDO (Mondo Disease Ontology); PKT (PheKnowlator); PRO (Protein Ontology); PW (Pathway Ontology); SO (Sequence Ontology); VO (Vaccine Ontology); UBERON (Uber-Anatomy Ontology)."
  ],
